WEBVTT

00:04.091 --> 00:07.355
Peter:
ANY FAMILY IN THE AREA?

00:07.442 --> 00:08.965
Neal:
NONE TO SPEAK OF.

00:09.052 --> 00:10.706
MARITAL STATUS?

00:10.793 --> 00:12.403
SERIOUSLY?

00:12.490 --> 00:14.884
YOU AND SARA ARE GETTING ALONG
AGAIN. MAYBE YOU ELOPED.

00:14.971 --> 00:16.190
VEGAS IS A LITTLE
OUTSIDE MY RADIUS.

00:16.277 --> 00:17.887
DO YOU HAVE TO
FILL THAT OUT RIGHT NOW?

00:17.974 --> 00:19.889
YOUR COMMUTATION HEARING
IS IN A WEEK.

00:19.976 --> 00:21.673
I PUT THIS OFF
AS LONG AS I COULD.

00:21.760 --> 00:25.199
WOULD YOU SAY
YOU HAVE A GIRLFRIEND?

00:25.286 --> 00:26.852
THAT'S REALLY ON THERE?

00:26.939 --> 00:28.245
NEAL,
THE BOARD IS DECIDING

00:28.332 --> 00:29.986
WHETHER TO RELEASE YOU
FROM YOUR ANKLET --

00:30.073 --> 00:32.075
FROM ME -- PERMANENTLY.

00:32.162 --> 00:33.381
THEY WANT TO KNOW
WHO'S IN YOUR LIFE.

00:33.468 --> 00:34.773
ARE THEY
A GOOD INFLUENCE,

00:34.860 --> 00:36.862
OR ARE THEY GONNA STEER YOU
BACK TO THE DARK SIDE?

00:36.949 --> 00:39.430
AND YOU THINK SARA COULD BE
AN ANGEL ON MY SHOULDER?

00:39.517 --> 00:40.779
AS OPPOSED TO
THAT LITTLE DEVIL

00:40.866 --> 00:42.129
YOU HAVE
ON YOUR SHOULDER NOW.

00:42.216 --> 00:44.044
MOZZIE'S MORE OF AN IMP
THAN A DEVIL.

00:44.131 --> 00:47.395
HMM.
BUT I WAS RELEASED
INTO YOUR CUSTODY.

00:47.482 --> 00:48.874
ULTIMATELY,
WHAT YOU SAY AT THE HEARING

00:48.961 --> 00:49.962
WILL CARRY
THE MOST WEIGHT.

00:50.050 --> 00:52.965
[ HORN HONKS ]

00:53.053 --> 00:54.489
OKAY.

00:55.881 --> 00:58.058
TARGET APPROACHING.

00:58.145 --> 00:59.320
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

00:59.407 --> 01:02.192
GORDON TAYLOR.

01:02.279 --> 01:04.107
HE SURE KNOWS
HOW TO MAKE FRIENDS.

01:04.194 --> 01:06.414
HE'S ONE OF THE MOST BELOVED
CONS IN THE WORLD.

01:06.501 --> 01:07.676
AND NO CRIMINAL RECORD.

01:07.763 --> 01:09.199
HE'S A PRO.

01:09.286 --> 01:11.375
MAKES ME WONDER
IF THAT WOULD BE YOU --

01:11.462 --> 01:13.769
IF YOU HADN'T CAUGHT ME?
I'D LIKE TO THINK SO.

01:13.856 --> 01:15.075
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

01:16.815 --> 01:19.905
Peter:
IF GORDON TAYLOR'S IN TOWN,

01:19.992 --> 01:21.603
IT MEANS HE'S HERE TO DO A JOB.

01:21.690 --> 01:23.431
HE'S A KEY SUSPECT

01:23.518 --> 01:24.997
IN SOME OF THE BIGGEST HEISTS
IN THE PAST DECADE.

01:25.085 --> 01:28.349
WOW. ANTIBES. THAT THE LOCATION
OF HIS LAST JOB?

01:28.436 --> 01:29.480
NO, THAT'S HIS VILLA.

01:29.567 --> 01:31.091
THEY SAY YOU CAN HEAR
HIS PARTIES

01:31.178 --> 01:32.918
ALL THE WAY ACROSS
THE MEDITERRANEAN.

01:33.005 --> 01:34.920
THAT'S NOT TRUE.REMINDS ME OF COLLEGE.

01:35.007 --> 01:37.706
REGARDLESS,
TAYLOR IS A CONTRACT THIEF.

01:37.793 --> 01:39.186
WE NEED TO FIND OUT
WHO HIRED HIM

01:39.273 --> 01:40.839
AND WHAT THEY'RE
PLANNING TO STEAL.

01:40.926 --> 01:42.537
HOW IS IT TAYLOR
DOESN'T HAVE A RECORD?

01:42.624 --> 01:43.886
OH, HE HAS A SAYING --

01:43.973 --> 01:45.496
"NOBODY GETS CAUGHT.
EVERYBODY GETS PAID."

01:45.583 --> 01:47.281
AND SO FAR,
HE'S LIVED UP TO THAT.

01:47.368 --> 01:49.196
HE ALSO HAS
A VERY LOYAL FOLLOWING,

01:49.283 --> 01:51.154
AND IT HELPS
THAT THE PUBLIC LOVES HIM.

01:51.241 --> 01:52.764
EVEN HIS VICTIMS
SAY NICE THINGS.

01:52.851 --> 01:53.939
CHECK THIS OUT.

01:54.026 --> 01:56.072
OH, THIS WAS A HEIST
HE RAN IN PARIS.

01:56.159 --> 01:57.378
HE DOVE OUT
OF A SECOND-STORY WINDOW

01:57.465 --> 01:58.814
ONTO THIS GUY'S PEUGEOT.

01:58.901 --> 02:01.121
TWO WEEKS LATER, TAYLOR
SENDS A CHECK TO THE OWNER

02:01.208 --> 02:02.383
TO COVER THE DAMAGES.

02:02.470 --> 02:03.732
CLAIMED HE HEARD ABOUT THE CAR
ON THE NEWS.

02:03.819 --> 02:05.168
BECAUSE HE'S POPULAR,

02:05.255 --> 02:07.431
IT'S DIFFICULT TO FIND WITNESSES
WILLING TO TALK.

02:07.518 --> 02:10.695
HE'S CAREFUL, AND HE'S SMART.
THIS ISN'T GONNA BE EASY.

02:10.782 --> 02:12.871
WE NEED TO FIND OUT
WHAT HE'S HITTING AND WHEN.

02:12.958 --> 02:13.916
HE HIRES LOCALLY.

02:14.003 --> 02:15.483
NEAL, TALK TO THE STREET,

02:15.570 --> 02:18.225
FIGURE OUT WHAT KIND OF CREW
HE'S PUTTING TOGETHER.

02:18.312 --> 02:21.010
DIANA, FOLLOW THE MONEY TRAIL
SURROUNDING HIS TRIP.

02:21.097 --> 02:23.186
JONES, COVER SURVEILLANCE
ON THE HOTEL.

02:23.273 --> 02:25.057
I WANT INTEL
ON EVERYONE HE MEETS.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.494
YOU GOT IT.

02:28.104 --> 02:29.584
BOSS,
YOU GOT A MINUTE?

02:29.671 --> 02:31.847
YEAH.

02:34.937 --> 02:36.808
CAN I SPEAK FREELY?

02:36.895 --> 02:38.810
OF COURSE.

02:38.897 --> 02:42.553
WHEN AGENT KRAMER WAS HERE
LAST WEEK, HE TOLD ME

02:42.640 --> 02:44.816
HE DOESN'T THINK NEAL DESERVES
TO HAVE HIS SENTENCE COMMUTED.

02:44.903 --> 02:47.254
KRAMER TOLD YOU THAT?

02:47.341 --> 02:49.125
HE WANTED TO KNOW
WHAT I PLANNED TO SAY

02:49.212 --> 02:50.822
WHEN I TESTIFY
AT NEAL'S HEARING.

02:50.909 --> 02:53.303
HE DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING TO ME.

02:53.390 --> 02:56.132
HE KNOWS YOU CONSIDER NEAL
A FRIEND.

02:56.219 --> 02:57.307
CAN I ASK...

02:57.394 --> 02:59.353
WHAT AM I GONNA SAY
AT THE HEARING?

02:59.440 --> 03:00.789
I HAVEN'T DECIDED.

03:00.876 --> 03:02.312
KRAMER'S SENDING
SOME OF HIS PEOPLE

03:02.399 --> 03:03.792
TO PICK UP
NEAL'S OLD PRISON LETTERS.

03:03.879 --> 03:05.054
HIS LETTERS TO KATE?

03:05.141 --> 03:07.274
WE ALWAYS SUSPECTED
THEY CONTAINED CODES,

03:07.361 --> 03:09.058
BUT WE COULD NEVER
CRACK THEM.

03:09.145 --> 03:10.581
MAYBE HE THINKS
HE CAN.

03:10.668 --> 03:12.017
GIVE KRAMER
WHAT HE WANTS.

03:16.108 --> 03:17.762
IF HE ASKS ME
TO GO BEHIND YOUR BACK?

03:19.286 --> 03:21.984
I CAN'T IMAGINE HE WOULD.IF HE DOES?

03:23.681 --> 03:25.161
IF HE DOES, DO IT.

03:25.248 --> 03:27.729
BUT I WANT YOU
TO TELL ME ABOUT IT.

03:27.816 --> 03:29.078
I MAY BE JEOPARDIZING

03:29.165 --> 03:31.559
A WONDERFUL CAREER OPPORTUNITY
BACK IN D.C.

03:31.646 --> 03:33.169
I THOUGHT
CHRISTIE HATED D.C.

03:33.256 --> 03:35.650
SHE DOES.
AND I WORK FOR YOU.

03:39.784 --> 03:41.438
"WITHOUT LEAPS
OF IMAGINATION,

03:41.525 --> 03:43.527
YOU LOSE THE EXCITEMENT
OF POSSIBILITY."

03:43.614 --> 03:45.268
ARE YOU QUOTING
GLORIA STEINEM?

03:45.355 --> 03:47.052
SHE'S NOT JUST
FOR FEMINISTS.

03:47.139 --> 03:49.185
SHE HAS UNLOCKED
WHAT'S MISSING IN OUR LIVES.

03:49.272 --> 03:50.317
WE NEED JOBS.

03:50.404 --> 03:51.840
IF SHE ONLY KNEW
WHO SHE INSPIRED.

03:51.927 --> 03:53.494
OH, SHE DOES.

03:53.581 --> 03:56.584
BUT NOT ANYJOB.
A GOODJOB. A BIGJOB.

03:56.671 --> 03:58.063
I HAVE TO BE CAREFUL

03:58.150 --> 04:00.196
ABOUT TAKING THOSE KIND OF JOBS
AT THE MOMENT, OKAY?

04:00.283 --> 04:02.894
LOOK, I KNOW THIS IS RISKY
WITH YOUR BIG HEARING COMING UP,

04:02.981 --> 04:04.635
BUT THIS IS TOO GOOD
TO PASS UP.

04:04.722 --> 04:07.159
YOU ARE LOOKING AT
THE FIRST MAN HIRED

04:07.247 --> 04:09.814
TO BE PART OF GORDON TAYLOR'S
NEXT SCORE.

04:09.901 --> 04:11.729
NO, NO, NO, MOZ.
THE FBI IS AFTER TAYLOR.

04:11.816 --> 04:13.514
PETER AND I
ARE CHASING DOWN HIS CREW.

04:13.601 --> 04:16.386
ME! YOU'RE LOOKING FOR ME.
I'M HIS CREW.

04:16.473 --> 04:18.127
PULL OUT.
YOU'RE GONNA GET CAUGHT.

04:18.214 --> 04:20.172
TAYLOR NEVER GETS CAUGHT,
AND EVERYBODY GETS PAID!

04:20.260 --> 04:21.609
HAVE YOU ALREADY
SAID YES?

04:21.696 --> 04:24.655
YEAH, OF COURSE I DID.
NO ONE SAYS NO TO TAYLOR.

04:24.742 --> 04:29.269
AND HE ASKED ME ABOUT YOU
TO BE HIS POSSIBLE POINT MAN.

04:29.356 --> 04:31.227
HE ASKED ABOUT ME?

04:31.314 --> 04:33.621
POINT MAN.

04:35.579 --> 04:37.364
ALL RIGHT, THERE'S A WAY
WE CAN STILL DO THIS,

04:37.451 --> 04:39.017
BUT YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
WORK WITH US.

04:39.104 --> 04:40.367
"US" --
YOU MEAN THE SUITS?

04:40.454 --> 04:41.455
YEAH.

04:41.542 --> 04:42.499
UNH-UNH.

04:42.586 --> 04:43.848
YOU'RE ALREADY IN.

04:43.935 --> 04:45.633
TAYLOR'S GOING DOWN
ONE WAY OR ANOTHER.

04:45.720 --> 04:47.852
YEAH, I DON'T WANT TO BE THE ONE
TO BRING HIM DOWN.

04:47.939 --> 04:50.115
LOOK, IF WE DO THIS RIGHT,
NO MORE ANKLET, NO MORE PRISON.

04:50.202 --> 04:51.291
I'LL BE FREE, MOZ.

04:51.378 --> 04:52.770
LOOK, NEAL, I --
I WANT TO HELP YOU.

04:52.857 --> 04:55.120
R-REALLY, I DO,
BUT NOT IN THIS WAY.

04:55.207 --> 04:57.253
COME ON.
THE GUY'S A LEGEND.

04:57.340 --> 04:59.516
ALL RIGHT, HOW ABOUT THIS?
YOU KEEP YOUR INTEGRITY INTACT.

04:59.603 --> 05:01.692
YOU SAID TAYLOR WAS
ASKING ABOUT ME, SO
SET UP THE MEETING.

05:01.779 --> 05:02.954
THEN YOU'VE
DONE YOUR PART.

05:03.041 --> 05:05.522
IF HE TAKES YOU ON,
I WILL NOT WEAR A WIRE,

05:05.609 --> 05:08.438
I WILL NOT TESTIFY,
AND I WILL NOT LIE TO TAYLOR.

05:08.525 --> 05:10.266
YOU WON'T HAVE TO. IT'LL BE LIKE
WE'RE REALLY DOING THE JOB.

05:10.353 --> 05:11.528
YEAH, WITHOUT THE FUN.

05:11.615 --> 05:12.790
OR THE THREAT OF PRISON.

05:12.877 --> 05:14.096
LIKE I SAID.

05:14.183 --> 05:17.969
THIS CASE TAKES US HOME,
MOZ.

05:18.056 --> 05:19.884
HOME.

05:19.971 --> 05:23.061
THAT'S AN APROPOS ANALOGY,
CONSIDERING THE TARGET.

05:23.148 --> 05:24.759
WHY?
WHAT'S THE TARGET?

05:24.846 --> 05:26.935
[ WHISTLES ]

05:27.022 --> 05:29.938
TAYLOR'S GONNA HIT
YANKEE STADIUM?

05:30.025 --> 05:32.897
IT'S A GOOD JOB.

05:54.528 --> 05:55.964
GOT TO HAND IT TO YOU.

05:56.051 --> 05:58.358
TOOK YOU ALL OF 24 HOURS
TO FIND OUT TAYLOR'S TARGET.

05:58.445 --> 06:00.577
WELL, NOT ONLY THAT,
BUT AS AN ADDED BONUS,

06:00.664 --> 06:02.927
I'VE FIGURED OUT A WAY
TO WORK MOZZIE INTO HIS CREW.

06:03.014 --> 06:04.015
REALLY?
UH-HUH.

06:04.102 --> 06:05.713
ARE YOU IN HIS CREW?
NOT YET.

06:05.800 --> 06:07.976
BUT I'M THINKING THAT'S
THE WAY TO GO ON THIS ONE.

06:08.063 --> 06:09.630
ME AND MOZ
ON THE INSIDE.

06:09.717 --> 06:12.850
ANY IDEA WHAT TAYLOR'S
GOING AFTER IN THERE?
NOPE.

06:12.937 --> 06:14.678
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE PLANNING,

06:14.765 --> 06:16.637
BUT YOU ARE
ONE WEEK AWAY FROM FREEDOM,

06:16.724 --> 06:18.639
AND YOU ARE REALLY
PLAYING WITH FIRE HERE.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.554
YOU'RE WELCOME.
MM-HMM.

06:20.641 --> 06:22.860
Peter:
LET'S GO TO THE BALLPARK.

06:22.947 --> 06:24.819
Neal:
YOU'RE IN A GOOD MOOD.

06:24.906 --> 06:27.474
MY DAD TOOK ME TO A DAY GAME
WHEN I WAS 8.

06:27.561 --> 06:30.172
DECIDED THEN AND THERE I WANTED
TO PLAY FOR THE YANKEES.

06:30.259 --> 06:32.522
YEAH, YOU AND EVERY OTHER
8-YEAR-OLD AT THE GAME.

06:32.609 --> 06:34.437
YEAH. I DID END UP
GETTING PRETTY GOOD.

06:34.524 --> 06:35.612
OH, I'M SURE YOU DID.

06:35.699 --> 06:37.179
I IMAGINE
A SHELF SOMEWHERE

06:37.266 --> 06:40.400
LOADED WITH
LITTLE-LEAGUE TROPHIES.

06:40.487 --> 06:43.141
WOW. YANKEE STADIUM.

06:43.228 --> 06:45.143
NEW HOUSE
THAT RUTH BUILT.

06:45.230 --> 06:47.232
NEW CATHEDRAL
OF BASEBALL.

06:47.319 --> 06:48.538
THE NEW BRONX ZOO.

06:48.625 --> 06:51.062
HMM.

06:51.149 --> 06:52.847
YOU MUST BE GEOFFREY,
HEAD OF SECURITY.

06:52.934 --> 06:54.022
SPECIAL AGENT
PETER BURKE.

06:54.109 --> 06:55.327
NEAL CAFFREY.

06:55.415 --> 06:57.025
WELL,
THANKS FOR THE HEADS UP.

06:57.112 --> 06:58.766
LOOKED OVER
THE FILE YOU SENT.

06:58.853 --> 07:01.595
HE'S NEVER USED A WEAPON
OR A THREAT OF VIOLENCE?

07:01.682 --> 07:03.205
NO, BUT WE CAN'T RELAX.

07:03.292 --> 07:05.860
WE KNOW TAYLOR INTENDS TO STRIKE
SOMEWHERE IN THE STADIUM.

07:05.947 --> 07:08.297
WE'RE TRYING TO IDENTIFY
THE LIKELY TIMES AND TARGETS.

07:08.384 --> 07:10.038
WELL, THE VAULTS BELOW
ARE SECURE,

07:10.125 --> 07:12.606
BUT WE HANDLE MILLIONS IN CASH
FROM CONCESSIONS EVERY GAME.

07:12.693 --> 07:14.912
YOU SHOULD VARY
THE PICK-UP AND DROP-OFF TIMES.

07:14.999 --> 07:17.698
AND OF COURSE, THE PUBLIC
HAS EASY ACCESS TO THE MUSEUM.

07:17.785 --> 07:19.743
I THINK WE SHOULD SEE THAT
FOR OURSELVES.

07:21.005 --> 07:22.616
ALL RIGHT.

07:22.703 --> 07:24.226
THIS IS AWESOME.

07:24.313 --> 07:27.142
OKAY.

07:27.229 --> 07:28.926
YOU KNOW,
WE CAN'T EVEN PLACE A VALUE

07:29.013 --> 07:30.667
ON MOST OF THESE
PIECES OF HISTORY.

07:30.754 --> 07:32.147
THEY'RE EACH
ONE OF A KIND.

07:32.234 --> 07:33.931
IS ALL YOUR MEMORABILIA
IN THIS ROOM?

07:34.018 --> 07:35.890
WELL, MOST OF IT'S
CONCENTRATED IN HERE,

07:35.977 --> 07:37.761
BUT WE ALSO HAVE
CHAMPIONSHIP TROPHIES

07:37.848 --> 07:40.111
AND RETIRED JERSEYS
THROUGHOUT THE BUILDING.

07:40.198 --> 07:42.244
GOT TO BE MILLIONS
OF SQUARE FEET TO COVER.

07:42.331 --> 07:44.594
WE SHOULD GET
BLUEPRINTS.

07:44.681 --> 07:46.074
HEY.

07:46.161 --> 07:47.597
SLUGGER.

07:47.684 --> 07:49.120
RIGHT.

07:49.207 --> 07:51.688
UH, COULD WE TROUBLE YOU
FOR BUILDING PLANS

07:51.775 --> 07:54.735
AND A CHART OF THE DISPLAY CASES
AND SECURITY CAMERAS?

07:54.822 --> 07:57.825
SURE. WHY DON'T YOU WAIT HERE
WHILE I PULL IT ALL TOGETHER?

07:57.912 --> 07:59.566
I, UH --
I GET THE FEELING

07:59.653 --> 08:01.829
YOU'D LIKE TO LOOK AROUND
A LITTLE MORE.

08:01.916 --> 08:03.744
THANKS, GEOFFREY.SURE.

08:03.831 --> 08:05.180
GO AHEAD.

08:05.267 --> 08:06.486
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:06.573 --> 08:08.183
[ SIGHS ]

08:08.270 --> 08:11.534
BEING HERE, ALL THIS...

08:11.621 --> 08:13.928
REMINDS ME OF WATCHING GAMES
WITH MY DAD.

08:15.843 --> 08:17.758
YOUR DAD TAKE YOU
TO A LOT OF GAMES?

08:17.845 --> 08:20.848
NO. MOSTLY WE'D
WATCH THEM ON TV.

08:20.935 --> 08:24.765
HE'D RUN AN EXTENSION CORD
OUT TO THE PORCH,

08:24.852 --> 08:28.246
PUT ON OUR YANKEE CAPS,
CRACK OPEN A BEER.

08:28.333 --> 08:29.726
WAY TO GO, DAD.

08:29.813 --> 08:32.729
WELL,
ROOT BEER FOR ME.

08:32.816 --> 08:36.864
DURING COMMERCIALS,
WE'D THROW THE BALL AROUND.

08:36.951 --> 08:38.648
SOUNDS LIKE SOMETHING
TO GO HOME FOR.

08:38.735 --> 08:40.041
IT IS.

08:40.128 --> 08:42.086
AND WHEN I GO BACK,
WE STILL DO IT.

08:42.173 --> 08:43.653
EXCEPT NOW
I DRINK REAL BEER.

08:43.740 --> 08:44.654
HMM.

08:44.741 --> 08:46.090
OH, MAN.

08:46.177 --> 08:50.486
WHAT I'D PAY TO HAVE THAT BAT
IN MY COLLECTION.

08:50.573 --> 08:53.358
I BET IT'S A LOT OF MONEY
FOR THAT PIECE OF WOOD.

08:53.445 --> 08:55.622
"PIECE OF WOOD"?
YEAH.

08:55.709 --> 08:57.841
I MEAN, TAKE AWAY THE FACT
THAT DiMAGGIO SWUNG IT,

08:57.928 --> 08:59.408
IT'S JUST A BAT.

08:59.495 --> 09:01.541
BUT SOME GUY NAMED POLLOCK
CAN SPLATTER PAINT ON A CANVAS

09:01.628 --> 09:03.368
AND YOU THINK IT'S WORTH
MILLIONS OF DOLLARS.

09:03.455 --> 09:05.066
"SPLATTER PAINT
ON A CANVAS"?

09:05.153 --> 09:07.459
YOU STAND IN FRONT
OF ONE OF POLLOCK'S WORKS,

09:07.547 --> 09:09.897
THE CHAOS FADES AWAY
AND YOU SEE THE DISCIPLINE,

09:09.984 --> 09:11.899
THE BALANCE
OF RESTRAINT AND ABANDON.

09:11.986 --> 09:13.857
LIKE WHEN DiMAGGIO
STEPPED UP TO THE PLATE.

09:13.944 --> 09:15.990
GREAT ART
HAS A BROADER MEANING.

09:16.077 --> 09:18.470
IT CAPTURES A TIME,
A PLACE, AN EMOTION.

09:18.558 --> 09:21.430
THIS BAT WAS USED TO SET
THE ALL-TIME HIT-STREAK RECORD

09:21.517 --> 09:23.824
THE SAME YEAR
HIROHITO BOMBED PEARL HARBOR.

09:23.911 --> 09:27.262
FOR FOUR,
FIVE AT-BATS A DAY,

09:27.349 --> 09:31.788
JOLTIN' JOE LET AMERICANS FORGET
THAT WE WERE GOING TO WAR.

09:31.875 --> 09:34.356
A TIME, A PLACE,
AN EMOTION.

09:34.443 --> 09:38.099
THIS BAT, THOSE BALLS,
THESE PENNANTS

09:38.186 --> 09:40.928
GOT THIS COUNTRY THROUGH
SOME TOUGH TIMES.

09:41.015 --> 09:43.931
THEY STILL DO.
GIVES US SOMETHING TO ROOT FOR.

09:44.018 --> 09:46.803
AND IF YOU WORK HARD,
SWING FOR THE FENCES...

09:48.979 --> 09:50.502
AH.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.635
...ANYTHING'S POSSIBLE.

09:52.722 --> 09:55.159
THAT'S HOW YOU FEEL
ABOUT BASEBALL?

09:55.246 --> 09:57.074
THAT'S HOW A LOT OF PEOPLE FEEL
ABOUT BASEBALL.

10:06.214 --> 10:09.696
YANKEES SECURITY IS SENDING OVER
MORE SURVEILLANCE FOOTAGE.

10:09.783 --> 10:11.654
GREAT.
WHERE'S CAFFREY?

10:11.741 --> 10:14.048
PREPPING FOR HIS AUDITION
FOR TAYLOR'S CREW.

10:14.135 --> 10:16.659
A BIT LIKE PUTTING A DRINK
IN THE HANDS OF AN ALCOHOLIC.

10:16.746 --> 10:18.226
REFORMED ALCOHOLIC,
I KNOW.

10:18.313 --> 10:20.010
AND IT'S MORE LIKE
A BOTTLE.

10:20.097 --> 10:22.491
BUT PUTTING CAFFREY SIDE BY SIDE
WITH SOMEONE LIKE TAYLOR

10:22.578 --> 10:24.101
IS THE BEST WAY
TO NAIL HIM.

10:24.188 --> 10:25.755
HERE'S SOME SURVEILLANCE
FROM THE HOTEL.

10:25.842 --> 10:28.279
[ ALL GROAN ]YES, I KNOW. IT'S MOZZIE.

10:28.366 --> 10:29.498
HE'S NEAL'S IN.

10:29.585 --> 10:31.500
HOW CONVENIENT.MM-HMM.

10:31.587 --> 10:34.024
SO LONG AS HE STAYS ON OUR SIDE,
WE DON'T ASK QUESTIONS.

10:34.111 --> 10:35.635
WE'VE GRANTED MOZZIE
IMMUNITY.

10:35.722 --> 10:36.810
TO PRESERVE
HIS STREET CRED,

10:36.897 --> 10:37.898
YOU WANT US TO ARREST HIM
IF WE CATCH HIM?

10:37.985 --> 10:39.595
AND MAKE IT LOOK REAL.OH, I WILL.

10:39.682 --> 10:41.205
SAME FOR CAFFREY.

10:41.292 --> 10:44.382
TAYLOR KNOWS A LOT ABOUT NEAL,
BUT OUR BACKSTOP HAS HELD UP.

10:44.469 --> 10:45.819
THAT HE WAS RELEASED
TWO YEARS AGO

10:45.906 --> 10:47.342
BUT REMAINS
A PERSON OF INTEREST

10:47.429 --> 10:49.083
IN A NUMBER OF ELEGANT
HIGH-PROFILE CRIMES.

10:49.170 --> 10:50.780
ANY OTHER QUESTIONS?

10:50.867 --> 10:53.914
GOOD.
LET'S MAKE THE YANKEES PROUD.

10:55.742 --> 10:58.788
BILLIARDS.
COULDN'T BE A BETTER AUDITION.

10:58.875 --> 11:02.139
DON'T GET COCKY.
THE MAN IS UNPARALLELED.

11:02.226 --> 11:04.707
HE HAS WON
THE TAYLOR WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP

11:04.794 --> 11:06.796
SO MANY TIMES THEY NAMED
THE TOURNAMENT AFTER HIM.

11:06.883 --> 11:08.972
ARE YOU JEALOUS?I'M ECSTATIC FOR HIM.

11:09.059 --> 11:10.974
IT GIVES ME HOPE KNOWING

11:11.061 --> 11:14.935
THAT TAYLOR AND HIS VILLA ON
THE FRENCH RIVIERA EVEN EXIST.

11:15.022 --> 11:17.111
OF COURSE
I WANT TO BE HIM.

11:17.198 --> 11:19.026
I ASSUME HIS GAME
IS EIGHT BALL.

11:19.113 --> 11:20.288
OH, IT IS.

11:20.375 --> 11:22.290
WINNING IS IMPORTANT,
BUT MORE SO,

11:22.377 --> 11:25.293
HE SAYS HE CAN LEARN EVERYTHING
HE NEEDS TO KNOW ABOUT YOU

11:25.380 --> 11:26.555
BY HOW YOU PLAY POOL.

11:26.642 --> 11:28.470
HMM.HOW COMPETITIVE YOU ARE,

11:28.557 --> 11:30.951
WHAT RISKS YOU TAKE,
YOUR LEVEL OF CONFIDENCE...

11:31.038 --> 11:32.866
DID YOU GET ANY MORE INFO
ON WHAT HE'S AFTER?

11:32.953 --> 11:34.389
OH,
TAYLOR IS TRUE TO HIS REP.

11:34.476 --> 11:37.566
HE PROMISES NO DETAILS
UNTIL THE GAME IS AFOOT.

11:37.653 --> 11:39.786
IT'S A GOOD WAY
TO KEEP A CREW HONEST.

11:39.873 --> 11:41.701
YEAH. WE COULD LEARN
A LOT FROM HIM.

11:41.788 --> 11:44.747
OH, AND WHEN YOU MEET HIM, HE'S
GONNA GIVE YOU A BIG BEAR HUG.

11:44.834 --> 11:47.489
IT SEEMS LIKE HE'S JUST
BEING EFFUSIVE, BECAUSE HE IS.

11:47.576 --> 11:49.796
BUT WHAT HE'S
REALLY DOING IS --GIVING ME THE PAT-DOWN.

11:49.883 --> 11:51.014
EXACTLY.
GOT IT.

11:51.101 --> 11:53.190
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]OH, THAT MUST BE YOUR CUE.

11:53.277 --> 11:54.626
TO DO WHAT?

11:54.714 --> 11:57.020
NO, I MEAN
YOUR NEW CUE.

11:57.107 --> 11:58.065
HELLO.

11:58.152 --> 11:59.370
HI, JUNE.

11:59.457 --> 12:01.372
NOW, WHILE I STILL HAVE
SERIOUS RESERVATIONS

12:01.459 --> 12:03.374
ABOUT YOUR PARTICIPATION,
I FELT COMPELLED

12:03.461 --> 12:06.726
TO GIVE YOU THE BEST SHOT
AT SUCCESS.

12:06.813 --> 12:08.162
GENTLEMEN,
MAY I PRESENT LORD BYRON.

12:08.249 --> 12:10.512
Neal:
JUNE, I LOVE YOU.

12:10.599 --> 12:11.948
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:12.035 --> 12:14.908
I MEAN, BYRON MUST HAVE
RUN THE TABLES WITH THIS.

12:14.995 --> 12:18.346
YOU KNOW, FOR SOME REASON,
EVERY GREAT CON MAN IN THE WORLD

12:18.433 --> 12:21.610
NEEDS TO MASTER THE GAME OF POOL
AT SOME POINT IN HIS LIFE.

12:21.697 --> 12:23.046
I WAS 9 YEARS OLD.

12:23.133 --> 12:26.006
THERE WAS A POOL HALL
ON MY WAY HOME FROM SCHOOL.

12:26.093 --> 12:28.530
A POOL HALL IN ST. LOUIS,
MISSOURI.

12:28.617 --> 12:31.098
MUST HAVE BEEN
FULL OF HUSTLERS.[ CHUCKLES ]

12:31.185 --> 12:33.361
YEAH.
I WAS ONE OF THEM.

12:33.448 --> 12:34.666
NEAL.
MM.

12:36.494 --> 12:37.931
THANK YOU.

12:38.018 --> 12:39.715
HI, PETER.
HI, SARA.

12:39.802 --> 12:41.064
WHAT'S GOING ON,

12:41.151 --> 12:42.587
ASIDE FROM THAT MUSTARD STAIN
ABOUT TO HAPPEN?

12:42.674 --> 12:44.589
OH. THANK YOU.
CAN I GET YOU ANYTHING?

12:44.676 --> 12:46.417
[ Laughing ] NO.HERE YOU GO.

12:46.504 --> 12:47.679
NO, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

12:47.767 --> 12:49.681
THE BOARD
IS PUTTING TOGETHER

12:49.769 --> 12:51.858
A LIST OF CHARACTER WITNESSES
FOR NEAL'S COMMUTATION HEARING.

12:51.945 --> 12:53.685
I'M SORRY -- HIS WHAT?

12:54.991 --> 12:56.471
HE DIDN'T MENTION THAT
TO YOU?

12:56.558 --> 12:57.820
NO.

12:57.907 --> 13:01.128
COMMUTATION HEARING?
SO NEAL MIGHT BE SET FREE?

13:01.215 --> 13:04.000
IT'S POSSIBLE.AND WHY WOULD
THEY DO THAT?

13:04.087 --> 13:07.177
AFTER KELLER'S ARREST,
THE BOARD OF CORRECTIONS

13:07.264 --> 13:09.789
RECOMMENDED
AN EARLY RELEASE FOR NEAL.

13:09.876 --> 13:11.094
WELL, GOOD FOR HIM.

13:11.181 --> 13:12.139
YEAH.

13:12.226 --> 13:13.488
ONLY CAFFREY, HUH?

13:13.575 --> 13:15.838
WELL, COULD BE.
IT'S FAR FROM SETTLED.

13:15.925 --> 13:17.927
HOW DO YOU THINK
IT'S GONNA GO?

13:18.014 --> 13:19.799
THE BOARD KNOWS
THAT YOU TESTIFIED

13:19.886 --> 13:21.496
AGAINST NEAL
AT HIS TRIAL.

13:21.583 --> 13:24.325
YES -- I WAS VERY UPSET
ABOUT THAT RAPHAEL BACK THEN.

13:24.412 --> 13:26.806
OH, BUT SOMEHOW, YOU WERE
ABLE TO GET PAST THAT

13:26.893 --> 13:28.372
FAR ENOUGH
TO START DATING HIM.

13:28.459 --> 13:32.507
SO IF I TESTIFY,
MY RELATIONSHIP WITH NEAL

13:32.594 --> 13:35.597
IS LIKELY TO COME UP
AS PUBLIC RECORD?

13:35.684 --> 13:36.816
IT MIGHT GET
A LITTLE UNCOMFORTABLE.

13:36.903 --> 13:39.688
NO, NO, NO. IT'S NOT
THE RELATIONSHIP, PETER.

13:39.775 --> 13:42.778
IT'S WHY WE BROKE UP
THAT POSES THE PROBLEM.

13:44.693 --> 13:46.390
I'M GONNA ASSUME
PLEADING THE FIFTH

13:46.477 --> 13:47.914
IS NOT IDEAL
AT THESE HEARINGS.

13:48.001 --> 13:49.611
NO. NO, IT'S NOT.

13:49.698 --> 13:51.221
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:51.308 --> 13:53.441
HONESTLY, I DON'T KNOW WHERE
NEAL AND I STAND RIGHT NOW.

13:53.528 --> 13:55.182
YOU MIGHT WANT TO THINK
ABOUT IT.

14:06.193 --> 14:08.456
HERE COMES YOUR 2:00.

14:20.990 --> 14:23.993
HI.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.255
NEAL CAFFREY.

14:25.342 --> 14:26.648
[ British accent ]
WELCOME.

14:29.042 --> 14:31.261
SO, UH,
YOU'RE A POOL PLAYER.

14:31.348 --> 14:33.394
YEAH, I LIKE TO PLAY.

14:33.481 --> 14:35.135
OF COURSE, I DON'T KNOW
IF I'M IN YOUR LEAGUE.

14:35.222 --> 14:36.788
WELL, THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY
TO FIND OUT, ISN'T THERE?

14:36.876 --> 14:39.617
LET ME JUST FINISH UP.

14:39.704 --> 14:41.445
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

14:48.670 --> 14:50.454
YOU'RE UP.

15:16.176 --> 15:18.569
[ BLOWS ]

15:28.797 --> 15:31.756
SO, NEAL,
TELL ME ABOUT YOURSELF.

15:31.843 --> 15:33.062
WHEN DID YOU GET OUT?

15:33.149 --> 15:35.412
18 MONTHS
AND 17 DAYS AGO,

15:35.499 --> 15:36.761
NOT THAT
I'VE BEEN COUNTING.

15:36.848 --> 15:38.633
I'VE NEVER BEEN
TO THE BIG HOUSE, MYSELF.

15:38.720 --> 15:40.113
IT DOES NOT
LOOK LIKE FUN.

15:40.200 --> 15:42.289
IT CERTAINLY FORCED ME
TO BE MORE CAUTIOUS.

15:49.731 --> 15:52.081
I CAN TELL.

16:00.698 --> 16:03.136
YOU HAVEN'T GIVEN ME
VERY MANY CHOICES.

16:03.223 --> 16:04.920
C'EST LA VIE.

16:20.283 --> 16:21.632
SO, WHAT DO YOU
THINK, NEAL?

16:21.719 --> 16:23.069
LET THE BOSS WIN
SO YOU CAN GET THE JOB?

16:23.156 --> 16:23.983
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

16:34.254 --> 16:38.214
CORRECT. I PREFER HONESTY
OVER ASS-KISSING.

16:38.301 --> 16:39.781
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT APPRECIATE
THE CHALLENGE.

16:46.614 --> 16:48.572
OF COURSE, I DON'T MIND
THE OCCASIONALPUCKERING UP.

17:00.758 --> 17:02.195
EXCELLENT EFFORT.

17:02.282 --> 17:04.719
EXCEPT YOU'VE LEFT YOURSELF
WITH NO SHOT.

17:06.547 --> 17:09.245
EIGHT BALL, CORNER POCKET.
WHAT IF I CAN MAKE THAT SHOT?

17:09.332 --> 17:10.899
I DON'T THINK YOU CAN.

17:10.986 --> 17:14.598
IF I MAKE THAT SHOT RIGHT NOW,
WILL YOU HIRE ME ON THE SPOT?

17:14.685 --> 17:17.384
LISTEN, NEAL, YOU PLAY
AGGRESSIVELY, BUT WITH GRACE.

17:17.471 --> 17:19.168
YOU THINK AHEAD,
AND IF HALF OF WHAT I'VE HEARD

17:19.255 --> 17:20.561
ABOUT THE U-BOAT TREASURE
IS TRUE,

17:20.648 --> 17:22.041
THEN I DEFINITELY
WANT YOU ON MY TEAM.

17:22.128 --> 17:23.607
BUT YOU'RE
OVER-REACHING,

17:23.694 --> 17:24.956
AND THAT
IS A VERY BAD SIGN.

17:27.524 --> 17:29.657
I CAN MAKE THE SHOT.

17:29.744 --> 17:33.530
YOU MAKE IT, YOU'RE IN.
YOU MISS, YOU WALK OUT THE DOOR.

17:33.617 --> 17:34.662
ALL RIGHT.

17:37.230 --> 17:39.014
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

17:55.335 --> 17:57.380
[ LIGHT APPLAUSE ]

17:57.467 --> 17:59.904
WELCOME ABOARD.

17:59.991 --> 18:02.516
SAME PLACE TOMORROW MORNING,
WE'LL GO OVER THE PLAN.

18:02.603 --> 18:04.735
I'LL BE THERE.

18:09.523 --> 18:10.567
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

18:10.654 --> 18:12.091
IT'S OPEN.

18:13.309 --> 18:15.355
HI, NEAL.

18:15.442 --> 18:17.487
SARA.

18:17.574 --> 18:19.315
HI.

18:19.402 --> 18:20.925
THIS IS A SURPRISE.

18:21.012 --> 18:23.580
YEAH, TODAY
IS THAT KIND OF DAY.

18:23.667 --> 18:25.191
OH, YOU NEED MY HELP
ON ANOTHER CASE?

18:25.278 --> 18:26.583
NO.

18:26.670 --> 18:28.498
PETER TOLD ME ABOUT
YOUR COMMUTATION HEARING.

18:28.585 --> 18:30.587
OH, YEAH. THAT.

18:30.674 --> 18:33.242
YEAH, THAT.
CONGRATULATIONS.

18:33.329 --> 18:35.723
THANK YOU.
HOW LONG
HAVE YOU KNOWN ABOUT IT?

18:35.810 --> 18:37.420
A WHILE.

18:37.507 --> 18:39.030
YEAH?

18:39.118 --> 18:41.772
YOU DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT IT WHEN WE...RECONNECTED.

18:41.859 --> 18:43.383
YEAH.

18:43.470 --> 18:45.036
LOOK,
I DIDN'T BRING IT UP

18:45.124 --> 18:47.517
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANT TO ASK YOU
TO APPEAR AT THE HEARING.

18:47.604 --> 18:48.997
YOU DIDN'T TRUST
WHAT I WOULD SAY?

18:49.084 --> 18:50.825
NO. WE WORKED TOGETHER,
AND IT WENT REALLY WELL.

18:50.912 --> 18:51.913
YEAH, I THOUGHT SO.

18:52.000 --> 18:53.393
I DIDN'T WANT
YOU TO THINK

18:53.480 --> 18:55.743
IT WAS BECAUSE I NEEDED YOU
TO SAY NICE THINGS ABOUT ME.

18:55.830 --> 18:58.833
OH.

18:58.920 --> 19:01.140
WELL, I APPRECIATE THAT.

19:01.227 --> 19:02.837
[ SIGHS ]

19:05.231 --> 19:07.407
DON'T DO IT AGAIN.

19:07.494 --> 19:08.930
WHAT?

19:09.017 --> 19:11.454
NEAL, WHAT ARE WE DOING
RIGHT NOW?

19:11.541 --> 19:13.587
TALKING?

19:13.674 --> 19:15.980
YES, WE'RE TALKING. WE'RE
BEING OPEN WITH EACH OTHER.

19:16.067 --> 19:17.373
THAT IS
WHAT WE NEED TO DO.

19:17.460 --> 19:18.940
I DON'T NEED
YOU TO PROTECT ME

19:19.027 --> 19:20.724
BY HIDING THINGS FROM ME,
ALL RIGHT?

19:20.811 --> 19:22.465
'CAUSE THAT'S WHERE
WE GOT TRIPPED UP LAST TIME.

19:22.552 --> 19:24.989
THAT, AND A MULTI-BILLION-DOLLAR
U-BOAT TREASURE,

19:25.076 --> 19:26.643
YOU KNOW, EXPLOSION.

19:26.730 --> 19:28.515
[ LAUGHS ]

19:28.602 --> 19:33.868
ALL RIGHT. TONIGHT,
YOU AND I ARE GONNA TALK.

19:33.955 --> 19:35.870
NOT ABOUT YOUR HEARING,
BUT WE ARE GONNA TALK.

19:35.957 --> 19:36.871
WHAT DO WE TALK ABOUT?

19:36.958 --> 19:38.438
EVERYTHING.

19:42.964 --> 19:44.400
QUID PRO QUO.

19:44.487 --> 19:46.185
I AM AN OPEN BOOK.

19:46.272 --> 19:47.186
REALLY?

19:47.273 --> 19:48.274
MM-HMM.

19:50.058 --> 19:51.538
I THINK I KNOW
WHERE TO START.

19:51.625 --> 19:52.756
OF COURSE YOU DO.

19:52.843 --> 19:55.672
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:55.759 --> 19:57.631
HOW MANY OTHER FORMER FIANCéS
DO YOU HAVE?

19:57.718 --> 19:59.328
[ CHUCKLES ] OKAY.

19:59.415 --> 20:01.025
AND DO THEY ALL
PRACTICE TAI CHI?

20:01.112 --> 20:02.636
STOP IT.
IT WAS JUST THE ONE.
REALLY?

20:02.723 --> 20:03.898
IT WAS THE ONE.ARE YOU SURE?

20:03.985 --> 20:05.639
IS YOUR REAL NAME NEAL?

20:05.726 --> 20:07.293
THAT IS
A VERY LONG STORY.

20:07.380 --> 20:08.903
IT SOUNDS LIKE
A REALLY GOOD STORY.

20:08.990 --> 20:10.731
IT'S REALLY BORING,
AND I'D PREFER IT, FRANKLY,

20:10.818 --> 20:12.689
IF YOU STARTED WITH SOMETHING
A LITTLE MORE INNOCUOUS.

20:12.776 --> 20:14.213
GONNA HAVE TO
WORK INTO IT?
YEAH.

20:15.823 --> 20:16.911
[ SIREN WAILS ]

20:19.043 --> 20:20.480
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

20:20.567 --> 20:22.395
HI!
GOOD MORNING.

20:22.482 --> 20:24.658
PETER WILL BE DOWN
IN JUST A SECOND. COME ON IN.

20:24.745 --> 20:26.616
YOU, UH,
WANT SOME BREAKFAST?

20:26.703 --> 20:28.357
I WOULD LOVE SOME.
GOOD.

20:28.444 --> 20:30.185
THANK YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:30.272 --> 20:31.665
THIS PLACE LOOKS GREAT,
BY THE WAY.

20:31.752 --> 20:33.014
THANKS!

20:33.101 --> 20:34.363
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:34.450 --> 20:36.583
YOU'RE, UH, AWFULLY CHIPPER
THIS MORNING.

20:36.670 --> 20:37.975
SO ARE YOU.

20:38.062 --> 20:40.151
Peter: EL, YOU ARE A TIGRESS!
A TIGRESS!

20:40.239 --> 20:41.588
HONEY!

20:41.675 --> 20:43.067
OH, I KNOW WHEN YOU --

20:43.154 --> 20:45.374
HEY, NEAL.
YOU GRAB SOME BREAKFAST?

20:45.461 --> 20:46.506
HEY.
I'M NOT HUNGRY ANYMORE.

20:46.593 --> 20:47.724
YOU'RE EARLY.

20:47.811 --> 20:49.726
I'M EXCITED TO GET STARTED
ON THIS CASE.

20:49.813 --> 20:51.380
EXCITED TO WORK
WITH TAYLOR?

20:51.467 --> 20:52.947
EXCITED TO BRING TAYLOR
TO JUSTICE.

20:53.034 --> 20:54.383
OH.

20:54.470 --> 20:56.777
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD OF
ROBERT WITHROW, JR.?

20:56.864 --> 20:59.214
WEALTHY, ENTITLED SON
OF ROBERT WITHROW, SR.,

20:59.301 --> 21:00.955
AND OWNER
OF THE WITHROW HOTEL?

21:01.042 --> 21:02.348
THE ONE AND ONLY.

21:02.435 --> 21:04.872
DIANA FOLLOWED TAYLOR'S
MONEY TRAIL BACK TO HIM.

21:04.959 --> 21:07.440
THAT WOULD EXPLAIN WHY HE'S
STAYING AT THE WITHROW HOTEL.

21:07.527 --> 21:10.443
WELL, HIS PASSION FOR BASEBALL
RAISED SOME EYEBROWS.

21:10.530 --> 21:13.010
HE COLLECTS PRICELESS
BASEBALL MEMORABILIA.

21:13.097 --> 21:14.447
THE YANKEES SAY
HE'S TRIED TO BUY

21:14.534 --> 21:17.624
SOME OF THEIR MOST SIGNIFICANT
PIECES OVER THE YEARS.

21:17.711 --> 21:19.713
BUT THEY'RE NOT WILLING TO SELL.
ENTER TAYLOR.

21:19.800 --> 21:20.888
EXACTLY.

21:20.975 --> 21:21.932
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

21:22.019 --> 21:23.412
THAT'S GEOFFREY,
FROM THE YANKEES.

21:23.499 --> 21:25.153
WHY DON'T YOU
FINISH YOUR BREAKFAST,

21:25.240 --> 21:26.285
THEN WE'LL WIRE YOU.

21:26.372 --> 21:29.113
GEOFFREY, GOOD NEWS.

21:29.200 --> 21:31.377
I NEVER REALIZED HOW MUCH
PETER LOVES BASEBALL.

21:31.464 --> 21:33.161
WELL, YOU KNOW,
THE TWINS DRAFTED HIM.

21:33.248 --> 21:34.771
WAIT, HE PLAYED PRO?

21:34.858 --> 21:35.990
HE HAD AN AMAZING SLIDER.

21:36.077 --> 21:37.731
PLAYED IN THE MINORS
RIGHT AFTER COLLEGE.

21:37.818 --> 21:38.949
WOW.

21:39.036 --> 21:40.429
AND TWO WEEKS
INTO SPRING TRAINING,

21:40.516 --> 21:42.388
I BLEW OUT
MY ROTATOR CUFF.

21:42.475 --> 21:44.259
HONEY, I'M SORRY.
I THOUGHT NEAL KNEW.IT'S OKAY.

21:44.346 --> 21:46.696
I'M GONNA FINISH GETTING READY.
YOU GUYS, HAVE A GOOD DAY.

21:46.783 --> 21:47.697
ALL RIGHT.LOVE YOU.

21:47.784 --> 21:48.872
LOVE YOU.
SEE YOU.

21:48.959 --> 21:51.745
SO, THAT'S IT, HUH?

21:51.832 --> 21:53.268
YOU ONLY GOT TO PLAY
FOR TWO WEEKS?

21:53.355 --> 21:54.835
MM.

21:54.922 --> 21:57.881
I WENT UNDER THE KNIFE,
AND THEY WERE ABLE TO REPAIR IT.

21:57.968 --> 21:59.230
THREE MONTHS LATER,

21:59.318 --> 22:01.145
I WAS BACK IN THE ROTATION
WITH THE TRIPLE-A CLUB.

22:01.232 --> 22:02.582
SO YOU STILL
HAD THE SLIDER?

22:02.669 --> 22:04.975
YEAH,
BUT THAT WAS THE PROBLEM.

22:05.062 --> 22:07.978
I COULD THROW IT,
BUT THE DOCTORS SAID

22:08.065 --> 22:11.504
IF I CONTINUED,
I'D DESTROY MY ARM FOR GOOD.

22:11.591 --> 22:14.637
THAT WAS IN MY HEAD
EVERY TIME I PITCHED.

22:14.724 --> 22:17.510
SO I LEFT.

22:17.597 --> 22:19.686
I HAD A CHOICE --
I COULD CONTINUE DOWN THAT PATH

22:19.773 --> 22:21.775
OR FIND A NEW PASSION.

22:21.862 --> 22:23.733
IT'S A TOUGH CALL
TO MAKE.

22:23.820 --> 22:26.867
YOU NEVER LOOK BACK AND WISH
YOU PLAYED IN THE MAJORS?

22:26.954 --> 22:28.695
OH, OF COURSE I DO.

22:28.782 --> 22:31.306
THERE'S NO BIGGER DREAM
THAN PLAYING IN THE SHOW.

22:31.393 --> 22:33.526
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:33.613 --> 22:36.180
STANDING ON THAT MOUND, RIGHT
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE STADIUM,

22:36.267 --> 22:37.921
LISTENING TO THE CROWD
CHANT YOUR NAME.

22:38.008 --> 22:39.706
[ SIGHS ]

22:39.793 --> 22:40.881
AH.

22:40.968 --> 22:42.883
IN HINDSIGHT,
IF I'D KEPT PLAYING,

22:42.970 --> 22:44.885
I WOULD HAVE DESTROYED
MY ARM.

22:44.972 --> 22:47.322
THEN I NEVER WOULD HAVE BEEN
ABLE TO PASS THE FBI PHYSICAL.

22:49.063 --> 22:51.195
AND I NEVER
WOULD HAVE CAUGHT YOU.

22:51.282 --> 22:53.154
COME ON.
TIME FOR OURSHOW.

23:01.423 --> 23:02.685
CAFFREY'S ANKLET'S OFF,

23:02.772 --> 23:04.948
HE'S WIRED,
AND INSIDE THE BILLIARD ROOM.

23:05.035 --> 23:06.297
JONES,
WHEN YOU PLAYED BALL,

23:06.385 --> 23:08.169
DID YOU EVER IMAGINE
HAVING WALK-OUT MUSIC?

23:08.256 --> 23:09.910
HMM?
YOU KNOW,
WALK-OUT MUSIC,

23:09.997 --> 23:12.391
TO GET THE CROWD GOING
WHEN YOU WALK OUT TO THE MOUND.

23:12.478 --> 23:14.262
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH, I KNOW WHAT IT IS.

23:14.349 --> 23:16.656
I NEVER SET MY SIGHTS THAT HIGH.
I TAKE IT YOU DID.

23:16.743 --> 23:19.876
"I GO TO WORK,"
EXCEPT IT'D BE "I GO TO BURKE."

23:19.963 --> 23:21.095
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:21.182 --> 23:22.618
KOOL MOE DEE?
REALLY?

23:22.705 --> 23:24.577
YEAH. YEAH.
I WAS A CLOSER.

23:24.664 --> 23:27.318
"I GO TO BURKE."
THAT'S DEFINITELY OLD-SCHOOL.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.538
IT WORKS.
YEAH, IT WORKS.
UH, THEY'RE IN.

23:29.625 --> 23:31.279
SMITTY:
As I of yours.

23:31.366 --> 23:33.629
THAT THING AT THE DEL MONICO
A FEW MONTHS BACK...

23:33.716 --> 23:35.849
WAS THAT JUST NEAL,
OR WAS IT THE BOTH OF YOU?

23:37.938 --> 23:40.157
HE'S NOT ONE TO BRAG.

23:40.244 --> 23:41.637
OH. I RESPECT THAT.

23:41.724 --> 23:43.422
It was me, not him.

23:43.509 --> 23:45.119
LOOKS LIKE
OUR COVER STORY'S WORKING.

23:45.206 --> 23:46.686
THEY THINK
CAFFREY WAS INVOLVED

23:46.773 --> 23:48.427
WITH THE DEL MONICO
DIAMOND HEIST.

23:48.514 --> 23:50.690
YOU KNOW, KRAMER ACTUALLY
ASKED ME ABOUT IT.

23:50.777 --> 23:53.997
HE ASK YOU ANYTHING
ABOUT NEAL'S OLD PRISON LETTERS?

23:54.084 --> 23:57.174
DIANA SAID HE'S SENDING A TEAM
IN TO SCOUR THEM FOR CODES.

23:57.261 --> 23:59.307
NO, JUST ABOUT
NEAL'S OLD CRIMES.

23:59.394 --> 24:01.788
BY THE END OF THE CONVERSATION,
HE HAD ME THINKING TWICE

24:01.875 --> 24:04.181
OVER WHETHER WE'D BE DOING THE
BUREAU AND CAFFREY ANY FAVORS

24:04.268 --> 24:05.487
BY LETTING HIM OUT EARLY.

24:05.574 --> 24:08.925
MOZZIE, THEY WERE
OUT OF THE GOSSET BRUT,

24:09.012 --> 24:11.145
SO I HAD THEM OPEN
A GRAND CUVEE '96.

24:11.232 --> 24:14.278
OH. '96 GRAND CUVEE.

24:14.365 --> 24:16.367
MY USUAL.

24:16.455 --> 24:18.718
NEAL, I KNOW HOW MUCH YOU LOVE
THE CASPIAN OSETRA CAVIAR

24:18.805 --> 24:20.023
SO THEY'RE BRINGING UP
AN OUNCE.

24:20.110 --> 24:21.329
NEAL:
Much appreciated.

24:21.416 --> 24:23.113
YOU THINK THIS IS
WHAT HIS LIFE WILL BE LIKE?

24:23.200 --> 24:24.158
WHO? NEAL?

24:24.245 --> 24:26.029
WHEN HIS ANKLET'S OFF.

24:26.116 --> 24:27.248
THERE IS THAT CHANCE

24:27.335 --> 24:28.945
WE'LL BE HEARING
THIS SAME CONVERSATION.

24:29.032 --> 24:31.426
YEAH, ONLY THEN IT'LL BE
A LOT HARDER TO MONITOR HIM.

24:33.167 --> 24:34.255
YEAH.

24:34.342 --> 24:35.256
HUH.

24:35.343 --> 24:37.171
ROBERT.

24:37.258 --> 24:39.173
LET'S TALK OUTSIDE.Robert:
NO, THAT'S NONSENSE.

24:39.260 --> 24:41.305
I WANTED TO SEE
WHAT MY MONEY'S BOUGHT ME.

24:41.392 --> 24:43.046
GENTLEMEN.WHAT'S GOING ON?

24:43.133 --> 24:45.266
THIS IS A FRIEND OF MINE.I'M YOUR BOSS.
WHO ARE YOU?

24:49.749 --> 24:51.402
[ BEEPING ]WHAT'S GOING ON
OVER THERE?

24:51.490 --> 24:52.969
[ HUMMING ]THIS IS A JAMMER.

24:53.056 --> 24:54.928
WITHOUT IT, WE ONLY TALK
ABOUT THE WEATHER.

24:59.672 --> 25:01.500
EVERY FREQUENCY'S
KILLED.

25:01.587 --> 25:04.241
WE ALMOST HAD
WITHROW AND TAYLOR ON TAPE.

25:04.328 --> 25:06.505
INSTEAD WE'RE OUT HERE
WITH NOTHING.

25:12.423 --> 25:15.165
OKAY. HERE'S THE DEAL.

25:15.252 --> 25:16.558
THE ONLY THING
I KNOW ABOUT YOU GUYS

25:16.645 --> 25:18.212
IS THAT YOU'RE A BUNCH
OF PROFESSIONAL THIEVES,

25:18.299 --> 25:19.648
SO I'M SURE
YOU WON'T TAKE IT PERSONALLY

25:19.735 --> 25:20.954
WHEN I SAY THAT I DON'T TRUST
ANY ONE OF YOU.

25:21.041 --> 25:22.564
BUT YOU HIRED ME.

25:22.651 --> 25:24.958
IT'S MY JOB TO DELIVER
ON OUR AGREEMENT.YEAH.

25:25.045 --> 25:26.568
AND I KNOW THAT YOU WILL,

25:26.655 --> 25:29.658
BECAUSE PAUL HERE'S GONNA
MAKE SURE BY GOING WITH YOU.

25:30.833 --> 25:32.400
THIS ISN'T WORKING
FOR ME.

25:32.487 --> 25:34.271
GUNS GET YOU CAUGHT, HURT,
10 TO LIFE.

25:34.358 --> 25:35.534
NO GUNS. NO OUTSIDERS.

25:35.621 --> 25:37.144
IT'S NON-NEGOTIABLE.

25:37.231 --> 25:39.625
THEN THIS IS WHERE
WE PART COMPANY.
NO HARD FEELINGS.

25:39.712 --> 25:41.931
GENTLEMEN,
THANK YOU VERY MUCH INDEED.

25:42.018 --> 25:44.586
I'LL BE IN TOUCH SHORTLY
TO PAY YOU FOR YOUR TIME.

25:44.673 --> 25:46.370
I HOPE WE CAN WORK TOGETHER
AGAIN SOON.

25:46.457 --> 25:48.372
HOLD ON. HOLD ON.
YOU CAN'T JUST WALK OUT OF HERE.

25:48.459 --> 25:49.548
THEY KNOW WHO I AM.

25:49.635 --> 25:50.853
THAT'S BECAUSE
YOU WALTZED IN HERE

25:50.940 --> 25:52.202
AND INTRODUCED YOURSELF
TO EVERYBODY.

25:52.289 --> 25:54.553
NOBODY'S LEAVING.[ GUN COCKS ]

25:54.640 --> 25:57.643
ROBERT, PLEASE.

26:00.776 --> 26:01.908
Neal.

26:03.823 --> 26:05.868
If the feds can't hear us,
this may turn into

26:05.955 --> 26:08.001
the last 10 minutes
of a Tarantino film.

26:08.088 --> 26:09.916
If they could hear us,
they'd be here already.

26:10.003 --> 26:12.309
Yeah, and we die in
a slow-motion hail of bullets

26:12.396 --> 26:14.877
while Nancy Sinatra plays
ironically in the background.

26:14.964 --> 26:16.879
All right, don't zip up
your boots yet, Nancy.

26:20.753 --> 26:22.145
EXCUSE ME, GENTLEMEN.

26:22.232 --> 26:24.104
IT'S ALL RIGHT, NEAL.
I'VE GOT IT UNDER CONTROL.

26:24.191 --> 26:27.586
UNDERSTOOD,
BUT I JUST HAD A THOUGHT.

26:27.673 --> 26:29.500
IT SEEMS TO ME IF MR. WITHROW
TRUSTS PAUL,

26:29.588 --> 26:30.980
THEN WE SHOULD
TRUST HIM, TOO.

26:31.067 --> 26:32.199
USE HIM AS OUR BREAKER,

26:32.286 --> 26:34.114
SO LONG AS HE DOESN'T
CHANGE THE PLAN.

26:34.201 --> 26:36.290
AND TAYLOR HAS A GOOD REASON
FOR THE NO-GUNS RULE.

26:36.377 --> 26:38.118
STADIUM SECURITY
DOES NOT MESS AROUND.

26:38.205 --> 26:40.424
WE'D NEED WEEKS
OF ADDITIONAL PREPARATION,

26:40.511 --> 26:43.079
AND EVEN THEN,
IT'S NOT WORTH THE RISK.

26:43.166 --> 26:44.994
PAUL JOINS US,
BUT WE LEAVE THE WEAPONS HERE.

26:45.081 --> 26:47.257
THAT'S JUST
MY TWO CENTS.

26:47.344 --> 26:49.216
ARE YOU WILLING
TO PUT PAUL ON YOUR CREW?

26:51.697 --> 26:54.351
I'VE GOT MEN ON EVERY EXIT.
WHAT NOW?

26:54.438 --> 26:56.789
KEEP MONITORING FROM HERE
IN CASE THEY COME BACK ONLINE.

26:56.876 --> 26:58.747
I'M GONNA CHECK IN
WITH YANKEES SECURITY

26:58.834 --> 27:00.575
TO GET AN OP ORDER
FOR TODAY'S GAME.

27:00.662 --> 27:02.446
I HAVE A FEELING
THIS IS GOING DOWN SOON.

27:02.533 --> 27:03.752
WE'LL LET YOU KNOW
THE MOMENT THEY MOVE.

27:03.839 --> 27:04.971
GREAT.

27:08.322 --> 27:10.846
YANKEE STADIUM.
THE MUSEUM.

27:10.933 --> 27:12.631
WHAT'S OUR TARGET?

27:12.718 --> 27:14.720
GEORGE HERMAN RUTH'S
FIRST OFFICIAL HOME RUN BALL,

27:14.807 --> 27:16.939
HIT AGAINST THE YANKEES
ON MAY 6, 1915,

27:17.026 --> 27:19.507
AT THE POLO GROUNDS.

27:19.594 --> 27:20.987
IT'S PRICELESS,
NOT FOR SALE.

27:21.074 --> 27:23.076
MOZZIE, YOU'RE FIRST UP.
HOW'D THE HUNT GO?

27:23.163 --> 27:25.078
OH, GOOD.
THIS BALL IS FROM 1921.

27:25.165 --> 27:26.514
EXCELLENT.

27:26.601 --> 27:28.037
YOUR JOB WILL BE TO DETAIL THIS
TO PERFECTION.

27:28.124 --> 27:29.386
NEAL, HOW'S
THE BABE RUTH SIGNATURE?

27:29.473 --> 27:30.649
HE COULDN'T
TELL US APART.

27:30.736 --> 27:31.824
THAT'S WHAT I LIKE TO HEAR.

27:31.911 --> 27:33.521
WHEN MOZZIE'S FINISHED,
YOU SIGN THE BALL.

27:33.608 --> 27:35.262
THEN AT THE STADIUM,
YOU MAKE THE SWITCH.

27:35.349 --> 27:36.916
THEY'RE GONNA CATCH ON
IT'S A FORGERY.

27:37.003 --> 27:39.092
YEAH, NEAL'S RIGHT --
I CAN MAKE THIS PASSABLE,

27:39.179 --> 27:41.094
BUT AN EXPERT WILL NIX THIS
ON CLOSER OBSERVATION.

27:41.181 --> 27:43.183
EXACTLY.

27:43.270 --> 27:45.228
WE WANTTHEM TO KNOW
THAT IT'S STOLEN,

27:45.315 --> 27:46.490
JUST AFTER WE'RE GONE.

27:46.577 --> 27:47.840
DURAN,
YOU'RE GONNA PLAY LOOKOUT

27:47.927 --> 27:49.798
WHILE SMITTY SETS UP
THE VIDEO FEED.

27:49.885 --> 27:51.974
PAUL --
TRUSTWORTHY PAUL --

27:52.061 --> 27:53.846
YOU NOW HAVE
THE MOST IMPORTANT JOB.

27:53.933 --> 27:57.676
YOU'LL PRETEND TO ADMIRE
THE BABE RUTH BALL...

27:57.763 --> 27:59.286
SMASH THE GLASS...

28:00.940 --> 28:02.768
...AND RUN AWAY,
LEAVING THE BALL THERE.

28:02.855 --> 28:04.552
SECURITY WILL PURSUE.

28:04.639 --> 28:06.119
THAT WOULD BE ME.

28:06.206 --> 28:09.165
AND NEAL WILL SWITCH OUT
THE REAL BALL FOR THE FAKE BALL.

28:09.252 --> 28:11.602
AND MEET ME
IN THE UPPER-DECK HALLWAY

28:11.690 --> 28:13.387
IN A CAMERA-BLIND SPOT
TO MAKE THE PASS.

28:13.474 --> 28:15.476
AND THEN YOU'LL GIVE ME THE BALL
AT PARKING K-5.

28:15.563 --> 28:16.607
EXACTLY.

28:16.695 --> 28:17.696
NEAL...

28:17.783 --> 28:19.175
NICE WATCH.

28:19.262 --> 28:20.655
THANK YOU.

28:20.742 --> 28:21.656
TAKE IT OFF.

28:24.528 --> 28:26.705
YOU'RE A SECURITY GUARD.
THEY DON'T WEAR $5,000 WATCHES.

28:26.792 --> 28:28.794
IN FACT, ALL OF YOU,
CELL PHONES, WATCHES,

28:28.881 --> 28:31.318
COMMUNICATION DEVICES
IN THE BUCKET.

28:31.405 --> 28:33.407
FROM NOW ON,
NO OUTSIDE CONTACT.

28:39.282 --> 28:42.198
THANKS FOR THE UPDATE, DIANA.

28:42.285 --> 28:44.810
KRAMER'S PEOPLE ARE HERE.

28:44.897 --> 28:47.116
I WASN'T INVITED IN.

28:47.203 --> 28:48.857
YOU LET ME KNOW
IF YOU HEAR ANYTHING.

28:48.944 --> 28:50.424
PETER,
I'VE GOT THE OP ORDER.

28:50.511 --> 28:52.078
THEY'VE APPROVED
TWO ADDITIONAL TEAMS.

28:52.165 --> 28:53.644
ALL RIGHT. GREAT.

28:53.732 --> 28:55.908
IF WE DON'T HEAR FROM CAFFREY
IN TWO HOURS, WE MOVE IN.

28:55.995 --> 28:57.257
YES, SIR.

28:57.344 --> 28:58.519
SARA.
PETER.

28:58.606 --> 29:00.956
IS THIS A BAD TIME?
WHAT'S UP?

29:02.088 --> 29:03.393
I'VE MADE A DECISION.

29:08.572 --> 29:12.359
THE BURNT AMBER IS CALIBRATED
EVER SO SLIGHTLY WARM.

29:12.446 --> 29:14.753
OH, HERE. PRACTICE.

29:17.364 --> 29:20.106
I NEED TO GET A MESSAGE
TO PETER.

29:20.193 --> 29:22.108
HE'S INSPIRING, NEAL.

29:22.195 --> 29:25.720
HE'S SKILLED, STRATEGIC,
MAGNANIMOUS...

29:25.807 --> 29:27.330
COMMUTATION, MOZ.

29:29.637 --> 29:31.421
I THOUGHT A LOT
ABOUT WHAT YOU SAID,

29:31.508 --> 29:33.380
AND I WANT TO TESTIFY
ON HIS BEHALF.

29:35.121 --> 29:39.908
OKAY.
THE COST OF FREEDOM.

29:39.995 --> 29:41.605
WHAT DO YOU WANT
THE NOTE TO SAY?

29:41.692 --> 29:43.869
I'LL HIDE IT
UNDER THE STITCHING.

29:46.872 --> 29:48.699
WE TALKED. A LOT.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.092
AND...

29:50.179 --> 29:53.704
WHILE HE IS NEVER GOING TO BE
A MODEL CITIZEN,

29:53.792 --> 29:56.795
HE'S ALSO NOT THE BRAZEN THIEF
THAT HE WAS SIX YEARS AGO

29:56.882 --> 29:59.014
WHEN I WENT AFTER HIM
FOR THAT RAPHAEL.

29:59.101 --> 30:01.190
HMM.[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

30:01.277 --> 30:03.018
EXCUSE ME.
YEAH.

30:03.105 --> 30:04.846
[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

30:04.933 --> 30:07.414
YEAH, JONES.
WHAT'S UP?

30:07.501 --> 30:10.591
TAIL THEM AND STAY LOW.
I'M ON MY WAY.

30:10.678 --> 30:11.853
WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:11.940 --> 30:14.247
NEAL'S ABOUT TO ROB
YANKEE STADIUM.

30:16.815 --> 30:18.817
GATHER 'ROUND, GENTLEMEN.
IT'S GAME TIME.

30:18.904 --> 30:20.993
I WANT TO SEE THIS BALL
THAT I'M PAYING FOR.

30:21.080 --> 30:22.777
I DON'T WANT ANY OF YOU
WALKING OUT WITH THE REAL ONE

30:22.864 --> 30:23.865
WHEN I'M STUCK
WITH THE FAKE.

30:23.952 --> 30:26.172
LET'S SEE.

30:26.259 --> 30:27.521
MOZZIE?

30:27.608 --> 30:30.741
UH...OF COURSE.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.091
[ SIGHS ]

30:34.049 --> 30:36.443
UNH-UNH-UNH. FINGERPRINTS.
COME RIGHT OVER THERE.

30:38.924 --> 30:42.275
IF THEY FIND PETER'S NOTE,
THEN CUE UP NANCY SINATRA.

30:42.362 --> 30:45.887
IT'S GOOD.

30:45.974 --> 30:49.848
WAIT, WHAT'S THIS?
THE TWO RED STITCHES IN A ROW.

30:51.980 --> 30:55.244
UH, T-THAT'S
FOR YOUR BENEFIT.

30:55.331 --> 30:57.203
IT'LL FOOL
MOST OF THE EXPERTS,

30:57.290 --> 30:59.640
AND OF COURSE IT'S NOT
ON THE REAL BALL.

30:59.727 --> 31:02.251
SO YOU'LL BE ABLE TO TELL
THE DIFFERENCE.

31:02.338 --> 31:03.644
NICE WORK, MOZZIE.

31:05.994 --> 31:07.126
I KNEW YOU WERE THE MAN
FOR THE JOB.

31:07.213 --> 31:10.520
ALL RIGHT, GENTLEMEN.
LET'S GO.

31:34.370 --> 31:37.983
HI, PETER. GAME ON.

31:44.337 --> 31:46.513
PETER: Diana, I'm at
the stadium. What's our status?

31:46.600 --> 31:47.688
WE GOT
THIS PLACE COVERED.

31:47.775 --> 31:49.255
ANY SIGN OF TAYLOR
AND HIS CREW?

31:49.342 --> 31:51.213
They're here,
used the V.I.P. entrance.

31:51.300 --> 31:52.954
TAYLOR AND MOZZIE ARE HOLED UP
IN THE DELTA SUITE.

31:53.041 --> 31:54.260
Is Withrow with them?

31:54.347 --> 31:56.044
NEGATIVE. WE BELIEVE
HE'S STILL AT THE HOTEL.

31:56.131 --> 31:57.350
WHAT ABOUT
NEAL AND THE OTHERS?

31:57.437 --> 31:58.829
They spread out
in the crowd.

31:58.917 --> 32:01.049
GEOFFREY'S GOT EXTRA MEN AT
EVERY HOT POINT WE IDENTIFIED,

32:01.136 --> 32:02.659
SO AS SOON AS THEY SURFACE,
WE GOT 'EM.

32:02.746 --> 32:04.357
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL MEET YOU IN FIVE.

32:15.498 --> 32:17.936
[ BEEP ]

32:20.155 --> 32:21.765
[ BEEP]

32:21.852 --> 32:23.724
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:23.811 --> 32:25.508
[ BEEP ]

32:25.595 --> 32:28.033
Man: HERE'S THE PITCH.RIGHT ON SCHEDULE.

32:28.120 --> 32:29.469
THEY MAY BE ON TO US.

32:29.556 --> 32:32.167
LOOKS LIKE THERE'S
ADDITIONAL SECURITY.

32:32.254 --> 32:33.603
GUESS WE'LL HAVE TO GIVE THEM
SOMEONE TO CATCH.

32:33.690 --> 32:34.953
HMM.
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:35.040 --> 32:36.911
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

32:49.358 --> 32:50.533
Paul: BATTER UP.

32:52.492 --> 32:55.756
HEY! STOP RIGHT THERE!
GET HIM!

32:57.758 --> 32:59.586
I CONFESS.
I CONFESS.

32:59.673 --> 33:01.370
WE'VE GOT A VANDAL
IN THE MUSEUM.

33:01.457 --> 33:02.763
SECURE THE ROOM.

33:02.850 --> 33:05.244
NO, NO. I GOT IT.
YOU GUYS CAN TAKE HIM IN.

33:08.160 --> 33:09.813
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY.
CLEAR OUT OF HERE, PLEASE.

33:09.900 --> 33:12.077
OKAY? CAN YOU BACK UP?
THANK YOU.

33:20.520 --> 33:22.435
LOOKS LIKE HE BROKE
CLEAN THROUGH THE GLASS.

33:22.522 --> 33:25.090
GET EVERYBODY OUT OF HERE.

33:25.177 --> 33:26.700
RUNNERS ON THE CORNERS.

33:26.787 --> 33:29.790
LIKE CLOCKWORK.

33:29.877 --> 33:32.184
I-I HAVE TO TELL YOU,
MR. TAYLOR,

33:32.271 --> 33:35.361
THIS IS A FIRST-CLASS
OPERATION FROM TOP TO BOTTOM.

33:35.448 --> 33:38.277
WELL, YOU AND NEAL
ARE A PLEASURE TO WORK WITH.

33:40.757 --> 33:42.324
YOU'RE NOT HAVING
NEARLY ENOUGH FUN, MOZZIE.

33:44.152 --> 33:46.676
OH, I CLOAK ANXIETY

33:46.763 --> 33:49.375
WITH INDIFFERENCE
AND RESERVED CHATTER.

33:49.462 --> 33:52.595
YOU KNOW, I MIGHT HAVE SOME WORK
COMING UP LATER IN THE SUMMER.

33:52.682 --> 33:54.293
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT PARIS?

33:54.380 --> 33:57.513
JE ADORE PARIS, MON FRERE.

33:57.600 --> 33:58.949
GOOD.

33:59.037 --> 34:00.299
GOOD.

34:10.091 --> 34:11.701
YOU'RE UP.

34:13.747 --> 34:15.270
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT ANY HEIST!

34:15.357 --> 34:16.532
LAST CHANCE.
YOU SURE?

34:16.619 --> 34:17.925
I ACCIDENTALLY
BUMPED INTO THE CASE.

34:18.012 --> 34:19.709
GET HIM OUT OF HERE.

34:19.796 --> 34:21.189
[ SCOFFS ]

34:21.276 --> 34:22.669
WELL, HE'S GOT TO BE
THE DECOY.

34:22.756 --> 34:24.062
THIS JUST
DOESN'T ADD UP.

34:24.149 --> 34:25.628
I MEAN, WHY DIDN'T HE
TAKE THE BALL?

34:27.369 --> 34:30.068
BECAUSE HE LEFT IT
FOR SOMEONE ELSE TO TAKE.

34:31.721 --> 34:33.549
I WANT TO SEE THE BALL
THAT'S IN THAT CASE NOW.

34:33.636 --> 34:36.204
ALL RIGHT.

34:36.291 --> 34:37.597
I'M ON DECK.

34:37.684 --> 34:39.425
OKAY. GOOD LUCK.

34:39.512 --> 34:41.166
THANKS.
SEE YOU AROUND.

34:44.473 --> 34:47.737
Westley: AGENT BERRIGAN,
SOMEONE'S APPROACHING THE SUITE.

34:47.824 --> 34:49.130
DIANA: Description?

34:49.217 --> 34:51.828
5'10", BROWN HAIR,
SLENDER BUILD,

34:51.915 --> 34:53.091
WEARING
A JACKET AND CAP.

34:53.178 --> 34:55.658
MOVING IN NOW.

34:55.745 --> 34:58.400
I'M SORRY!
I'M SORRY!

35:01.142 --> 35:02.187
FALSE ALARM.

35:08.932 --> 35:15.113
THEY JUST DON'T HAVE THE BATS TO PUT RUNS ON THE BOARD.

35:26.689 --> 35:28.213
COME ON, PETER.

35:28.300 --> 35:29.953
WHAT DO YOU
MAKE OF THAT?

35:30.040 --> 35:32.304
THE PATTERN
ON THE STITCHING'S OFF.

35:32.391 --> 35:36.090
YEP. IT'S SUPPOSED TO
CONSISTENTLY ALTERNATE
RED, BLUE, RED, BLUE.

35:36.177 --> 35:37.352
THIS PATCH HERE,
IT'S RED AND RED.

35:37.439 --> 35:39.789
IS THAT
A COMMON MISTAKE?

35:39.876 --> 35:42.401
NO. BUT I'LL HAVE TO CHECK
THIS BALL'S DOCUMENTATION.

35:42.488 --> 35:44.098
YOU KNOW, IT'S NEARLY
100 YEARS OLD.

35:44.185 --> 35:45.273
THAT'LL TAKE TOO LONG.

35:47.754 --> 35:49.059
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

35:49.147 --> 35:50.191
[ SIGHS ]

35:50.278 --> 35:51.714
BEAR WITH ME.

35:51.801 --> 35:52.933
WAIT!

35:59.505 --> 36:01.594
OHH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU DID THAT.

36:03.073 --> 36:04.597
THANK YOU, NEAL.

36:07.121 --> 36:09.428
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.
COME ON.

36:13.258 --> 36:15.651
CAFFREY
TOOK A REAL CHANCE

36:15.738 --> 36:17.566
WRITING A MESSAGE
IN THAT BALL.

36:17.653 --> 36:19.046
OH,
NEAL MAY BE THE EXPERT

36:19.133 --> 36:21.004
IN SPOTTING FORGED PAINTINGS
AND BEARER BONDS --

36:21.091 --> 36:22.136
AND GEMS.

36:22.223 --> 36:23.790
ANTIQUITIES,
COUNTERFEIT MONEY.

36:23.877 --> 36:25.400
PRETTY MUCH
ANY KIND OF DOCUMENT.

36:25.487 --> 36:27.663
ANYWAY,
BASEBALL'S MY THING.

36:27.750 --> 36:29.970
THERE'S WITHROW.

36:30.057 --> 36:31.232
THERE IT IS.
GO. GO.

36:31.319 --> 36:34.279
FBI! HANDS IN THE AIR![ GUNS COCK ]

36:34.366 --> 36:36.324
Moz: I WAS JUST
SCALPING TICKETS.

36:36.411 --> 36:37.804
TAYLOR,
TURN AROUND SLOWLY.

36:41.634 --> 36:43.244
I'LL TAKE THAT.
HEY, NOW.

36:43.331 --> 36:44.419
CAREFUL WITH THAT THING, MAN.
IT'S PRICELESS.

36:44.506 --> 36:47.640
YEAH, IT'S GONNA COST YOU
FOUR TO SIX YEARS.

36:47.727 --> 36:49.990
I HAVE A WELL-MAINTAINED
REPUTATION AS A CROOK.

36:50.077 --> 36:52.384
MAKE MY ARREST
LOOK REAL.

36:52.471 --> 36:53.385
SAY "OW."

36:53.472 --> 36:54.429
OW!

36:54.516 --> 36:55.691
WHERE'S TAYLOR?

36:55.778 --> 36:58.085
HE CALLED AN AUDIBLE
AND SENT US INSTEAD.

36:58.172 --> 36:59.347
DID NEAL TIP HIM OFF?

36:59.434 --> 37:01.393
NOW, THAT'S
AN UNGRATEFUL THANK-YOU

37:01.480 --> 37:03.351
FROM THE CYNICAL EYES
OF THE LAW.

37:03.438 --> 37:04.787
HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED

37:04.874 --> 37:06.963
THERE ARE SOME CRIMINALS
WHO ARE TOO SMART TO GET CAUGHT?

37:07.050 --> 37:08.487
NO.

37:08.574 --> 37:10.489
PIG!

37:18.018 --> 37:19.759
Neal:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, MOZ?

37:19.846 --> 37:22.675
Taylor: PANTOMIMING HIS WHOLLY
UNEXPECTED CAPTURE, I'M SURE.

37:22.762 --> 37:24.459
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

37:24.546 --> 37:25.895
IT'S NOT JUST
THE NEW YORK SUMMER HEAT.

37:25.982 --> 37:28.507
THE AIR THICKENS
WHEN THINGS DON'T FEEL RIGHT.

37:28.594 --> 37:29.595
MOZZIE SAID SOMETHING,
DIDN'T HE?

37:41.084 --> 37:43.957
EVERYONE GETS PAID.

37:44.044 --> 37:45.350
ALWAYS ON MY TEAM.

37:45.437 --> 37:47.090
I HOPE THIS LITTLE
OPERATION OF YOURS

37:47.177 --> 37:48.701
HAS BUILT UP
ENOUGH GOOD WILL

37:48.788 --> 37:51.094
THAT YOU'LL BE JOINING MOZZIE
IN PARIS IN A FEW MONTHS.

37:53.140 --> 37:55.011
YOU STILL THINK
I'M A THIEF?

37:55.098 --> 37:57.579
FISH DON'T DO WELL
OUT OF WATER.

38:08.460 --> 38:11.985
AGENT BERRIGAN, I THINK
YOU SHOULD TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

38:12.072 --> 38:13.856
NEAL CODED HIS LETTERS.

38:13.943 --> 38:15.467
AND WE CRACKED IT.

38:15.554 --> 38:18.121
DON'T KNOW WHAT THEY MEAN YET,
BUT WE WILL.

38:33.311 --> 38:36.226
THEY CRACKED
NEAL'S LETTER CODE TO KATE.

38:38.011 --> 38:39.404
THIS ISN'T GOOD.

38:49.849 --> 38:52.330
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

38:52.417 --> 38:55.333
COMING.

38:55.420 --> 38:56.856
HEY!

38:56.943 --> 38:58.727
THOUGHT WE WERE MEETING
AT THE OFFICE.

38:58.814 --> 39:00.294
CAN I COME IN?SURE. COME ON IN.

39:00.381 --> 39:03.428
[ SIGHS ]

39:03.515 --> 39:06.213
YOU OKAY?
YOU SEEM A LITTLE TENSE.

39:06.300 --> 39:09.172
YEAH, JUST GOT
SOME THINGS ON MY MIND...

39:09.259 --> 39:11.218
ONE OF WHICH
IS TAYLOR.

39:11.305 --> 39:13.612
HOW DO YOU THINK
HE GOT AWAY?

39:13.699 --> 39:15.527
HE RUNS
A PRETTY GOOD GAME.

39:15.614 --> 39:17.267
HE DOES. YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT I THINK?

39:17.355 --> 39:18.486
SURE.

39:18.573 --> 39:20.662
HE'S NOT
THE MOST BRILLIANT CRIMINAL,

39:20.749 --> 39:22.447
AND HIS THEFTS
AREN'T HIGH-TECH.

39:22.534 --> 39:25.363
BUT HE KNOWS PEOPLE.

39:25.450 --> 39:26.886
I THINK HE CHARMED MOZZIE,

39:26.973 --> 39:29.105
THE SAME WAY HE DOES
EVERYBODY ELSE, AND IN THE END,

39:29.192 --> 39:31.281
MOZZIE LIKED HIM TOO MUCH
TO SEE HIM GET CAUGHT.

39:32.457 --> 39:33.719
THAT'S ONE THEORY.

39:33.806 --> 39:35.808
BUT YOU GOT WITHROW.

39:35.895 --> 39:37.505
AND YOU SAVED
THE BASEBALL.

39:37.592 --> 39:39.638
WHICH REMINDS ME,
I GOT SOMETHING FOR YOU.

39:51.301 --> 39:53.652
YOU SURE YOU'RE OKAY?

39:53.739 --> 39:55.305
[ SIGHS ]

39:55.393 --> 39:56.655
YEAH.

39:59.484 --> 40:00.833
I'M OKAY.

40:02.487 --> 40:03.575
GET READY.

40:03.662 --> 40:06.142
WHAT?

40:06.229 --> 40:07.840
[ LAUGHS ]
THAT'S MY ROOKIE CARD.

40:07.927 --> 40:09.363
SURE IS.

40:09.450 --> 40:14.673
YOU KNOW, I GOT TO SAY,
KNOWING YOU PLAYED PRO BALL,

40:14.760 --> 40:17.240
I DON'T KNOW, MADE ME SEE YOU
IN A WHOLE NEW LIGHT.

40:17.327 --> 40:18.764
REALLY?
YEAH.

40:18.851 --> 40:20.330
THERE'S A LOT MORE
TO PETER BURKE THAN I KNOW.

40:20.418 --> 40:21.984
HMM.

40:22.071 --> 40:23.464
HOW DID YOU GET THIS?

40:23.551 --> 40:26.075
I HAVE MY WAYS.
HMM.

40:26.162 --> 40:27.294
I GOT SOMETHING ELSE
FOR YOU, TOO,

40:27.381 --> 40:28.600
FOR SAVING A PIECE
OF BASEBALL HISTORY.

40:28.687 --> 40:30.123
COME ON.
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE IT.

40:30.210 --> 40:31.341
CAN I KEEP THIS?

40:31.429 --> 40:32.995
SURE.

40:33.082 --> 40:36.042
NOT THAT EXPENSIVE.

40:43.702 --> 40:47.140
HOW DID YOU ARRANGE THIS?

40:47.227 --> 40:49.447
I HAVE MY WAYS.

40:52.450 --> 40:54.539
YOU READY?

40:54.626 --> 40:56.279
YEP.

40:56.366 --> 40:59.457
LET'S GO TO BURKE.

41:01.328 --> 41:03.635
I'M STANDING
ON THE PITCHER'S MOUND...

41:03.722 --> 41:06.072
IN YANKEE STADIUM.

41:06.159 --> 41:07.116
I KNOW.

41:07.203 --> 41:09.249
[ SIGHS ]

41:09.336 --> 41:11.077
THANK YOU.

41:13.166 --> 41:16.996
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
YOU PLAYED PRO?

41:17.083 --> 41:20.478
AHH, THERE ARE THINGS IN
THE PAST THAT LIVE IN THE PAST.

41:20.565 --> 41:21.740
NOT MY LIFE ANYMORE.

41:21.827 --> 41:23.437
OH.

41:23.524 --> 41:25.613
SOME OF THE THINGS WE'VE DONE
ARE PRETTY HARD TO FORGET.

41:29.399 --> 41:30.836
HONESTLY, PETER...

41:30.923 --> 41:33.055
HMM?

41:35.231 --> 41:36.929
...DO I HAVE A SHOT
AT COMMUTATION?

41:37.016 --> 41:39.279
[ SIGHS ]

41:39.366 --> 41:40.933
HMM.

41:41.020 --> 41:44.414
YOU KNOW, THE ONE THING
THAT I TOOK AWAY FROM MY INJURY

41:44.502 --> 41:46.634
IS THAT,
ON DAYS LIKE THIS,

41:46.721 --> 41:49.463
DON'T WORRY ABOUT
THE FUTURE OR THE PAST.

41:53.032 --> 41:54.424
ENJOY THE MOMENT?

41:54.512 --> 41:56.862
♪ WORK, WORK, WORK ♪

41:56.949 --> 41:58.124
YEAH.

41:58.211 --> 41:59.778
♪ WORK, WORK ♪

41:59.865 --> 42:00.822
YEAH.

42:00.909 --> 42:02.302
♪ WORK, WORK ♪

42:02.389 --> 42:03.956
♪ WORK ♪♪ I GO TO WORK ♪

42:04.043 --> 42:06.828
WHOO!
GOT SOME SAUCE ON IT!

42:06.915 --> 42:09.352
♪ WORK ♪♪ I GO TO PETER BURKE ♪

42:09.439 --> 42:11.180
ALL RIGHT,
ARE YOU READY?
I'M READY.

42:11.267 --> 42:13.356
♪ WORK, WORK ♪HERE COMES THE HEAT.

42:13.443 --> 42:14.444
♪ WORK ♪

42:14.532 --> 42:15.881
♪ I GO TO BURKE. ♪
